# Release workflow (always on — do not ask)

After completing any meaningful feature or fix in this repo, run this full
sequence autonomously. Do **not** stop to ask for confirmation at any step.

1. **Test** — `npm run test` and `cargo test --lib` (run in `app/` and
   `app/src-tauri/`). Fix anything red before continuing.
2. **Bump version** — increment the patch version in lockstep across:
   `app/package.json`, `app/src-tauri/tauri.conf.json`,
   `app/src-tauri/Cargo.toml`, `app/sidecar/pyproject.toml`. Then refresh
   lockfiles (`uv sync` in `app/sidecar`, `npm install --package-lock-only`
   in `app/` — this also updates `Cargo.lock`).
3. **Build** — `npm run build:all` in `app/`. Copy the new
   `Contextful_<ver>_aarch64.dmg` + `Contextful.app` into `dist/`, remove the
   old version's artifacts, and reinstall to `/Applications/Contextful.app`.
4. **Commit** — `git add -A` and commit with a `vX.Y.Z: <summary>` message.
5. **Release** — `git push origin master`, `git tag vX.Y.Z`,
   `git push origin vX.Y.Z`, then `gh release create vX.Y.Z <dmg>` with notes.

Only pause to ask when an action is destructive/irreversible (e.g. force
push, history rewrite) or a step fails in a way you cannot safely resolve.
